class Solution:
    def minimumTimeToInitialState(self, word: str, k: int) -> int:
        n = len(word)
        time = 1
        while True:
            # After time seconds, the first k*time characters are removed
            # We need to check if the remaining part of the word matches the start of the original word
            if k * time >= n:
                return time
            if word[k * time:] == word[:n - k * time]:
                return time
            time += 1
```

This solution works by simulating the process of removing the first `k` characters and checking if the remaining part of the string matches the start of the original string. The process continues until the word reverts to its initial state. The time taken to achieve this is returned.
